<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-7557] optimize LogManager.truncateFullyAndStartAt()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-7557</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a ReplicaFetcherThread calls LogManager.truncateFullyAndStartAt() for a partition, we call LogManager.checkpointLogRecoveryOffsetsInDir() and then Log.deleteSnapshotsAfterRecoveryPointCheckpoint() on all the logs in that directory. This requires listing all the files in each log dir to figure out the snapshot files. If some logs have many log segment files. This could take some time.&#160;The can potentially block a replica fetcher thread, which indirectly causes the request handler threads to be blocked.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13194536">KAFKA-7557</key>
